      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Looking at the roots can reveal a lot; healthy blueberry roots should be fine, white, and relatively firm. Excessive circling or matted roots suggest rootbound conditions, while fine, stringy roots may indicate nutrient stress. Tunnels or significant disruptions, other than those caused by earthworms, could point toward soil-borne pests or fungal diseases.",
